title: * Re: Q2E Troubleshoot/Finding CATER 155476
text: 3/9/22 Q2E Troubleshoot/Find - CATER 155476 1. In order to safely test/investigate Q2E magnet, we LOTO the next to magnets as follows: a. LOTO/ZVV magnets - S1E#1, S1E#2, Q3E#1, Q3E#2, Q2E, Q2E-L, Q2E-R b. Air Gap Q2E, Q2E-L, Q2E-R at the power supply c. Test/investigate: i. Apply external DC supply to Q2E +/- terminal, ramp up current to 40Amp. ii. Measure voltage across each quadrant of the magnet iii. This is to verify potential short or contact coil internal 1. The result shows magnet is behaved normal iv. Test complete, put back the safety pixy shielding glass 2. Continue T/S at the rack: a. Run the EMHP and trim the BOOST supply and monitor the loop back response and found the EMHP is oscillating while the two BOOST supply output combine reach EMHP output voltage. i. The system is oscillating because the BOOST supply RC loop component is set to fast response and the EMHP is slow. ii. The RC loop at BOOST Q2E-L, Q2E-R supply was re-optimized to a new value 1. Original value is R2 = 51.1k, C2 = 1uF 2. New value is R2 = 16.92k, C2 = 6uF iii. System is working and trim successfully. 3. Additional finding that will require further work a. The Transductor for Q2E-L is not response well while troubleshooting b. Swap the Aux and Reg connector at the transductor cassette and it works c. The Transductor Cassette maybe need to be changed on next PAMM PE/CH/AD
